REACTIONS:  7Be(n,n) (MT=2), 7Be(n,p) (MT=600), 7Be(n,d) (MT=650)  419 1451
and 7Be(n,alpha) (MT=800) calculated from R-matrix analysis of     419 1451
reactions in the 8Be system.                                       419 1451
                                                                   419 1451
IMPORTANT COMMENTS:  The range of the evaluation is for En         419 1451
up to 8.1 MeV. The MT=2 evaluation was obtained without fitting    419 1451
any experimental data on that reaction, although the reaction is   419 1451
constrained by isospin symmetry to 7Li(p,p) and 7Li(p,n), for      419 1451
which substantial data were entered. The MT=600 evaluation was     419 1451
obtained without fitting any experimental data on that reaction    419 1451
(except for a set of very low-energy data discussed below),        419 1451
although the reaction is constrained by time reversal symmetry to  419 1451
7Li(p,n), for which substantial data were entered. The MT=650      419 1451
evaluation was obtained without fitting any experimental data on   419 1451
that reaction, although the reaction is constrained by time        419 1451
reversal symmetry to 6Li(d,n), for which substantial data were     419 1451
entered for most of the energy region (except the highest          419 1451
energies), and via isospin symmetry to 6Li(d,p), for which         419 1451
substantial data were entered for the entire energy region.        419 1451
The MT=800 evaluation was obtained without fitting any             419 1451
experimental data on that reaction, although the reaction is       419 1451
constrained by isospin symmetry to 7Li(p,alpha) for which          419 1451
substantial data were entered.                                     419 1451
                                                                   419 1451
